   261	
   262	### Git Closeout (mandatory before next major task)
   263	
   264	Default policy: the main thread owns normal `git add`, `git commit`, and standard `git push`. Do not ask the user for routine authorization on those operations when the closeout boundary is coherent and no exception condition is active.
   265	
   266	1. `git status --short` — confirm scope and exclude unrelated dirty files
   267	2. Produce recommended commit message + file scope
   268	3. The main thread may execute normal `git add + git commit` once validation is clean and the closeout boundary is coherent
   269	4. The main thread may execute a normal `git push` after commit when hard gates pass and no exception condition is active
   270	5. Escalate to the user instead of proceeding when any exception condition is active:
   271	   - history-rewriting or destructive Git actions are required (`push --force`, branch deletion, reset, rebase with published history)
   272	   - the target remote or target branch is ambiguous or differs from the expected closeout path
   273	   - unrelated dirty files or an incoherent commit boundary remain in the working tree
   274	   - required hard gates failed or validation evidence does not match the diff
   275	   - protected paths or release-sensitive operations are involved
